---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="China Sourcing Guide"
  description="A practical China sourcing hub for overseas small business buyers looking for suppliers, markets, factories, and QC basics."
  canonical="/china-sourcing/"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="page-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">China sourcing</span>
      <h1>Find better suppliers and avoid beginner sourcing mistakes.</h1>
      <p>
        A buyer-focused knowledge hub for wholesale markets, factory visits, supplier verification, product samples,
        quotations, payment terms, and quality control.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Core topics</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>How to find suppliers in China as a small importer</li>
          <li>Yiwu Market vs Canton Fair vs Guangzhou wholesale markets</li>
          <li>Questions to ask a supplier before placing a sample order</li>
          <li>MOQ, EXW, FOB, lead time, packaging, and payment terms</li>
          <li>Basic QC checklist before shipment</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Service expansion path</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Supplier comparison templates</li>
          <li>Factory visit planning</li>
          <li>Inspection and shipment coordination referrals</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="notice-box">
          <h2>Start with intent</h2>
          <p>Content should separate tourist advice from buyer advice so Google and readers both understand the page.</p>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/china-sourcing-checklist-small-business/">Read sourcing checklist</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
